The paper proposes a new graph kernel for classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The kernel incorporates locational correspondence information and guarantees transitivity, which are related to pattern recognition and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed kernel is evaluated on standard graph-based datasets, which are often used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The paper also mentions incorporating information from all graphs under comparison, which could be related to data mining (cs.DM) or social networks (cs.SI).
